The paper focuses on analyzing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) used in classification of cars in autonomous vehicles. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as the paper deals with image classification. Additionally, the paper uses an image generator to produce synthetic pictures, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The visualization tools used in the analysis can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with autonomous driving (cs.RO) as it focuses on analyzing CNNs used in this field. Finally, the paper can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) as it deals with analyzing and testing a system used in autonomous driving.
